snippet.textDisplay:
I thought the song would go in a very different direction, considering the intro to it. The visuals and especially the mesmerizing dancer in the saari. It felt like it was going to be a very deep, textural and cultural piece, with a violin, and some sort of old theatrical sounding story like song.

But I liked the pop style too, but was hoping it was a theatrical story telling song that was "serious" and had heartbreak, not necessarily about love, but of culture. Missed opportunity in my opinion, because the intro was alluding to it, and it was sooo good.
